lly dragon raids, that something is a shot at the loot.  If that piece of loot happens to be the same piece you were after, then you're going to take a lot of shit if you don't give them a chance at it too.<br>
<br>
Best system I've seen for pally books/dragon scales on pickup dragon raids where the raid leader needs it is that raid leader rolls 500-1000 or something, rather than outright calling the item.  This lets all the other pallies and bards who came on the raid have a chance too, and still gives the raid leader a good shot at getting the item they've been working so hard for.<br>
<br>
As for your comment about guilds, I'd love to be able to do Vox or Naggy with a guild only, or even a guild (and friends) only raid, but thanks to Verant's idiotic level cap I can't.  Even my best friends, unless they are pallies or bards, just level right on up past 53.  Because they want the spells or the disciplines or the loots to make THEM more effective at everything else.  So unless you have a way to somehow turn back the clock, and make it possible to have a guild with enough of the right classes over 45 and under 53 to pull off a dragon when it spawns, better get used to doing them as pickups.  As it is, I think most guilds would be lucky to get 5 or 6 folks who could participate in the actual fight out for it, and maybe some higher people to buff and help with giants, and the rest is going to be pickups.<br>
<br>
